<item>
            <title>[LU-18951] remove llog params records when erasing filesystem</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18951</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;For an MGT that is used for many short-lived filesystems in which params are set with &quot;lctl set_param -P&quot;, the params llog contains all previous commands and they are replayed for all subsequent file systems.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could &quot;lctl erase_lcfg &amp;lt;fsname&amp;gt;&quot; also remove the entries for &amp;lt;fsname&amp;gt; in the params log?&lt;br/&gt;
We currently use &quot;lctl llog_print params&quot; then find the entries for the filesystem to erase and remove them with &quot;lctl llog_cancel&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="89411">LU-18951</key>
