                            <comment id="476941" author="adilger" created="Sat, 1 Nov 2025 04:50:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/58958&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/58958&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18951&quot; title=&quot;remove llog params records when erasing filesystem&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18951&quot;&gt;LU-18951&lt;/a&gt; utils: lctl lcfg_erase erase fsname params&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;) is &lt;em&gt;mostly&lt;/em&gt; fixing the problem, but it is intermittently failing the new conf-sanity test_250 on ZFS, where the config llog is sometimes still showing records for the deleted filesystem.  I don&apos;t know why that is happening, but I suspect it is a test or cache issue and not a functional issue with the patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
