                            <comment id="453626" author="adilger" created="Fri, 25 Apr 2025 04:06:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=defazio&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;defazio&quot;&gt;defazio&lt;/a&gt;, I don&apos;t see a reason why this &lt;em&gt;couldn&apos;t&lt;/em&gt; be done, especially if the &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lctl set_param -P&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; commands are properly including the &lt;tt&gt;&lt;em&gt;FSNAME&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/tt&gt; into the parameter so that they can be found later.  Essentially the &lt;tt&gt;jt_lcfg_erase()&lt;/tt&gt; code can iterate the params log and cancel each of the records with &lt;tt&gt;jt_llog_cancel()&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
